      "textOverrides": {
        "frame.name": "Dawnbringer",
        "bg.hand-size": "10",
        "content.notes": "- custom: \"Years of facing the horrors of the dark nights have taught you a vital lesson; preparation is the key to survival. At the start of each scenario, choose exactly %i%one%ie% item from %i%each%ie% of the three categories available exclusively to you:  %p_top:-2px%%ammo%%p% Ammo,  %utility% Utility, and %thrown% Thrown, they become immediately available to you at the start of the scenario.\"\n- custom: \"Your arsenal items do not count towards any standard item slots and do not prevent you from bringing any other items. Note that you are significantly weakened without your tools, spend them wisely.\"\n- divider: \n- custom: You have abilities that allow you to restore your items once used. Abilities may call for you to %recover% either a specific category (%ammo%, %utility%, %thrown%) item or any Arsenal %arsenal% item(s).\n- divider: \n- custom: Some abilities let you give an ally an item on use, instead of %lost% it. Whenever they use the item, return it to your %lost% pile."
      },
