      "retirementText": "N/A",
      "classDescription": "The few who outlasted the initial raids learned that survival required more than a high wall. Calling themselves Dawnbringers, these solitary mercenaries became the thin defense line between the settlement and the dark. Relying on cold iron, crude alchemy, and hand-crossbows, they view hunting not as a heroic adventure, but as a slow-burning retribution. They slip into the woods at night to dismantle threats before they ever reach the town gates, trading their blood and sanity for the promise of a quiet sunrise.",
